{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kp28cUNxbamTV99avGfYYR","type":"tool_result","content":"   200→    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n   201→    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n   202→    pendingLamports: string\n   203→  }\n   204→\n   205→GET  /referral/earnings            — Get detailed per-game earnings log\n   206→  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n   207→  Response: {\n   208→    items: [{\n   209→      roundId: string,\n   210→      gameType: string,\n   211→      refereeWallet: string,\n   212→      wagerLamports: string,\n   213→      earnedLamports: string,\n   214→      createdAt: string\n   215→    }],\n   216→    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n   217→  }\n   218→\n   219→POST /referral/claim               — Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n   220→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n   221→\n   222→GET  /referral/claim/:claimId      — Poll claim status\n   223→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   227→- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication <!-- gap: no referral routes registered -->\n   228→- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict) <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   229→- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   230→- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) <!-- gap: no API responses to verify -->\n   231→\n   232→### FR-8: Database Schema\n   233→\n   234→New tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n   235→\n   236→```sql\n   237→referral_codes (\n   238→  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   239→  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n   240→  code          TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,   -- player-chosen, 3-16 chars [a-z0-9-]\n   241→  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   242→  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   243→)\n   244→\n   245→referral_links (\n   246→  id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   247→  referrer_wallet TEXT NOT NULL,\n   248→  referee_wallet  TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- one referrer per player\n   249→  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   250→)\n   251→\n   252→referral_earnings (\n   253→  id                        SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   254→  referrer_wallet           TEXT NOT NULL,\n   255→  referee_wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   256→  round_id                  TEXT NOT NULL,\n   257→  game_type                 TEXT NOT NULL,\n   258→  wager_lamports            BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   259→  fee_lamports              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   260→  referrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   261→  referrer_rate_bps         INTEGER NOT NULL,\n   262→  referee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   263→  referee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- always 1000 for v1\n   264→  created_at                TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   265→  UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- idempotency: one earning per player per round\n   266→)\n   267→\n   268→referral_claims (\n   269→  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n   270→  wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   271→  amount_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   272→  status            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed')),\n   273→  tx_signature      TEXT,\n   274→  error             TEXT,\n   275→  requested_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   276→  processed_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n   277→)\n   278→\n   279→-- KOL custom referrer rates (overrides default 1000 bps)\n   280→referral_kol_rates (\n   281→  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   282→  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n   283→  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n   284→  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   285→  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   286→)\n   287→```\n   288→\n   289→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   290→- [x] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates all 5 tables -->\n   291→- [x] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 — referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   292→- [x] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:12 — code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   293→- [x] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — 6 indexes covering all wallet lookups and round_id -->\n   294→- [x] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:43-44 — CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round -->\n   295→- [x] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:67-68 — CHECK constraint chk_referral_claims_status -->\n   296→\n   297→### FR-9: Frontend — Routes, Pages, and Components\n   298→\n   299→All frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RV1VboAcMDf4MT4RSfBWWe","session_id":"3e0bba06-3e2a-40d1-8fc4-6fd6659fa3ce","uuid":"b0ca2272-54a0-47f9-a36a-f1c54ac50b02","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:47:05.680Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MzQrrFqV34Hq15v16Wb5mA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: [300] Referral System\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Priority | P1 |\n     9→| Track | Extended |\n    10→| NR_OF_TRIES | 5 |\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→A Hyperliquid-style referral system where any player can set a custom referral code, share it, and earn a perpetual share of the platform fee from every game their referred players complete. Referred players receive a benefit for joining via a referral link (see FR-3 for options). The system is entirely off-chain for v1 — no program changes required.\n    17→\n    18→## User Stories\n    19→\n    20→- As a player, I want to set a custom referral code so that I can invite friends and earn passive rewards from their gameplay\n    21→- As a new player, I want to use a referral code so that I receive a signup benefit (fee rebate or bonus reward)\n    22→- As a referrer, I want to see how many players I've referred and how much I've earned so that I can track my referral performance\n    23→- As a referrer, I want to claim my accumulated earnings so that I receive SOL in my wallet\n    24→- As an operator, I want to set custom referral rates for KOL wallets so that partnership agreements are honored\n    25→\n    26→---\n    27→\n    28→## Capability Alignment\n    29→\n    30→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented in Current Baseline\" → \"Referral and creator monetization systems\"\n    31→- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n    32→- **Planning bucket**: Extended\n    33→\n    34→## Required Context Files\n    35→\n    36→- `docs/DECISIONS.md` — fee structure (500 bps flat fee, single treasury via PlatformConfig)\n    37→- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/` — frontend entrypoint\n    38→- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` — on-chain fee constants (for reference, not modified)\n    39→- Backend settlement logic (settlement worker, DB schema)\n    40→\n    41→## Contract Files\n    42→\n    43→- No existing mocks — this is a new system\n    44→- API contract defined in FR-7 below\n    45→\n    46→---\n    47→\n    48→## System Invariants (v1)\n    49→\n    50→These invariants are non-negotiable for correctness and abuse resistance:\n    51→\n    52→1. **Single referrer binding:** each referee wallet can be linked to only one referrer wallet for life (unless operator manually unlinks via admin tooling outside v1 scope).\n    53→2. **No self-referral:** `referrer_wallet !== referee_wallet` enforced at API + DB layers.\n    54→3. **Lamports-only accounting:** all stored/transported monetary values use integer lamports (`BIGINT` in DB, string in JSON APIs).\n    55→4. **Atomic settlement + earning write:** referral earning insert must be in the same DB transaction as game settlement write.\n    56→5. **Idempotent async handlers:** referral queue handlers must use domain keys (`claim_id`, `round_id + referee_wallet`, etc.), never `event_queue.id`, for de-duplication.\n    57→6. **Exactly-once effect in practice:** queue may deliver at-least-once; side-effects must remain safe under replays.\n    58→7. **No on-chain protocol changes:** v1 referral economics remain off-chain and treasury-operated.\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→\n    62→## Functional Requirements\n    63→\n    64→### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n    65→\n    66→Any player with a connected wallet can set a referral code. No eligibility gate — open from day one.\n    67→\n    68→**Rationale:** The sybil incentive is negligible (max benefit from self-referral is 50 bps of wagered amount = referrer fee share, and self-referral is blocked on-chain). An eligibility gate hurts organic growth more than it prevents abuse.\n    69→\n    70→**Code format:**\n    71→- Player-chosen custom code: 3-16 characters, `[a-z0-9-]`, must be unique\n    72→- No auto-generation — the player always picks their own code\n    73→- URL format: `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}`\n    74→\n    75→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    76→- [ ] Authenticated player can set a referral code via API <!-- gap: routes/referral.ts does not exist -->\n    77→- [ ] Code is always player-chosen, 3-16 chars, validated against `[a-z0-9-]`, unique <!-- gap: no validation logic implemented -->\n    78→- [x] Each player has exactly one active code (setting a new one replaces the old one) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql UNIQUE(wallet) + db.ts:660 upsertReferralCode ON CONFLICT replaces -->\n    79→- [x] Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates table + db.ts:637 insertReferralCode -->\n    80→\n    81→### FR-2: Referral Linking\n    82→\n    83→When a player signs up or connects their wallet via a referral link (`taunt.bet/r/CODE`), they are permanently linked to the referrer. Alternatively, a player can manually enter a referral code in their settings.\n    84→\n    85→**Rules:**\n    86→- One referrer per player, immutable once set\n    87→- First code applied wins — cannot change referrer\n    88→- Self-referral blocked (same wallet cannot be both referrer and referee)\n    89→\n    90→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    91→- [ ] Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until the player authenticates <!-- gap: no /r/:code route in App.tsx -->\n    92→- [ ] On authentication, if the player has no referrer and a stored/submitted code exists, the link is created <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n    93→- [ ] Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page) <!-- gap: no POST /referral/apply endpoint or profile UI -->\n    94→- [x] Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 referee_wallet UNIQUE + db.ts:694 insertReferralLink throws on duplicate -->\n    95→- [ ] Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected <!-- gap: no API-level validation implemented -->\n    96→- [x] Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:17-22 + db.ts:694-701 insertReferralLink -->\n    97→\n    98→### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n    99→\n   100→Referred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable — every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.\n   101→\n   102→**Economics:**\n   103→- On a 1 SOL wager with 500 bps fee: fee = 0.05 SOL, referee rebate = 0.005 SOL\n   104→- Rebate is calculated and stored at settlement time, same transaction as the referrer earning\n   105→- Fee is charged in full on-chain — rebate accrues off-chain as claimable SOL\n   106→- Rebate shares the same claim flow as referrer earnings (unified pending balance per wallet)\n   107→\n   108→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   109→- [ ] After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` <!-- gap: no settlement hook in settle-tx.ts -->\n   110→- [ ] Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) <!-- gap: no calculation logic implemented -->\n   111→- [ ] Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) <!-- gap: no claim flow or balance calculation -->\n   112→- [ ] Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   113→- [ ] A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance <!-- gap: no balance aggregation logic -->\n   114→\n   115→### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n   116→\n   117→When a referred player completes a game, the referrer earns a share of the platform fee from that game. This is the core incentive loop.\n   118→\n   119→**Economics:**\n   120→- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n   121→- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n   122→- Source: platform fee — no new fees charged to players\n   123→- Duration: **permanent** — referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n   124→- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n   125→\n   126→**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n   127→\n   128→**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer → calculates earnings → inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n   129→\n   130→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   131→- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n   132→- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n   133→- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n   134→- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n   135→- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n   136→\n   137→### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n   138→\n   139→Referrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n   140→\n   141→**Stats view:**\n   142→- Total referred players\n   143→- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n   144→- Total wager volume from referrals\n   145→- Total earnings (all time)\n   146→- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n   147→- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n   148→\n   149→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   150→- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RV1VboAcMDf4MT4RSfBWWe","session_id":"3e0bba06-3e2a-40d1-8fc4-6fd6659fa3ce","uuid":"8e157adc-7916-424a-92ea-34e02c3dd400","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:47:05.702Z"}
