{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RV1VboAcMDf4MT4RSfBWWe","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary document.\n\n## Summary\n\nI found and read the referral migration file and backend configuration. Here are the exact schemas and patterns you requested:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **referral_claims Table Schema**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` (lines 56-68)\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n| `id` | UUID | PRIMARY KEY, DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() | Unique claim identifier |\n| `wallet` | TEXT | NOT NULL | Wallet claiming earnings |\n| `amount_lamports` | BIGINT | NOT NULL | Amount in lamports (integer) |\n| `status` | TEXT | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 'pending', CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed')) | Claim lifecycle state |\n| `tx_signature` | TEXT | NULL | Solana transaction signature (set when completed) |\n| `error` | TEXT | NULL | Error message if status = 'failed' |\n| `requested_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NOT NULL, DEFAULT now() | Claim request timestamp |\n| `processed_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NULL | Completion/failure timestamp |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `idx_referral_claims_wallet` on `(wallet, requested_at)` — for wallet-specific queries\n- `idx_referral_claims_status` on `(status)` WHERE status IN ('pending', 'processing') — for active claim polling\n\n---\n\n### 2. **referral_kol_rates Table Schema**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` (lines 78-84)\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n| `wallet` | TEXT | PRIMARY KEY | KOL wallet address |\n| `rate_bps` | INTEGER | NOT NULL | Custom referrer rate in basis points (e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee) |\n| `set_by` | TEXT | NOT NULL | Admin wallet that set the rate |\n| `created_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NOT NULL, DEFAULT now() | Creation timestamp |\n| `updated_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NOT NULL, DEFAULT now() | Last update timestamp |\n\n**Purpose:** Overrides the default 1000 bps referrer rate for KOL wallets (e.g., partnership agreements with higher shares)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Environment Variable Patterns for Referral Config**\n\n**Finding:** **No `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS` env var currently exists** in the backend config.\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n\nThe `Config` interface (lines 4-23) does NOT include a referral rate field. The backend loads config via:\n- `requireEnv(name: string)` — throws if env var missing\n- `process.env[name] ?? \"defaultValue\"` — optional with fallback\n- `parseInt()` for numeric values\n\n**Current pattern for optional integers with defaults:**\n```typescript\nexport function loadConfig(): Config {\n  return {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    workerPollIntervalMs: parseInt(\n      process.env.WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS ?? \"1000\",\n      10,\n    ),\n    minSolBalance: parseFloat(process.env.MIN_SOL_BALANCE ?? \"0.1\"),\n    // ... more fields ...\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**What needs to be added (based on spec):**\n- Add `referralDefaultRateBps: number` to the `Config` interface\n- Add parsing in `loadConfig()`:\n  ```typescript\n  referralDefaultRateBps: parseInt(\n    process.env.REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS ?? \"1000\",\n    10,\n  ),\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Related Referral Schema (from same migration)**\n\nThe migration also creates these supporting tables (already read above):\n\n- **`referral_codes`** — one custom code per wallet (3-16 chars, [a-z0-9-])\n- **`referral_links`** — immutable referrer→referee binding (one per referee)\n- **`referral_earnings`** — per-game tracking with `referrer_rate_bps` and `referee_rebate_rate_bps` (always 1000 for v1)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Default Rate Constants from Spec**\n\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md`:\n\n- **Default referrer rate:** 1000 bps of total fee (= 50 bps of wager)\n- **Referee rebate:** Always 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable)\n- **KOL override:** Stored in `referral_kol_rates.rate_bps`, applied at settlement time\n\n**Gap identified in spec (line 132):** \"Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) — gap: no config env var `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS`\"\n\n---\n\n**All file paths are absolute:**\n- Migration: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql`\n- Config: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n- DB interface: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n- Spec reference: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a90f86f6323eb61de (use SendMessage with to: 'a90f86f6323eb61de' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63122\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 136755</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e0bba06-3e2a-40d1-8fc4-6fd6659fa3ce","uuid":"58557dea-0d35-4470-a991-2619c06be0cd","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:47:17.906Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the referral migration file at sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql. I need to see the exact schema for:\n1. referral_claims table (columns, types, constraints)\n2. referral_kol_rates table (columns, types)\n\nAlso find any environment variable patterns - check if there's a config file or env parsing that shows how REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS might be loaded. Check the backend's index.ts or config files for env var patterns.","agentId":"a90f86f6323eb61de","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary document.\n\n## Summary\n\nI found and read the referral migration file and backend configuration. Here are the exact schemas and patterns you requested:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **referral_claims Table Schema**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` (lines 56-68)\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n| `id` | UUID | PRIMARY KEY, DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() | Unique claim identifier |\n| `wallet` | TEXT | NOT NULL | Wallet claiming earnings |\n| `amount_lamports` | BIGINT | NOT NULL | Amount in lamports (integer) |\n| `status` | TEXT | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 'pending', CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'processing', 'completed', 'failed')) | Claim lifecycle state |\n| `tx_signature` | TEXT | NULL | Solana transaction signature (set when completed) |\n| `error` | TEXT | NULL | Error message if status = 'failed' |\n| `requested_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NOT NULL, DEFAULT now() | Claim request timestamp |\n| `processed_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NULL | Completion/failure timestamp |\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `idx_referral_claims_wallet` on `(wallet, requested_at)` — for wallet-specific queries\n- `idx_referral_claims_status` on `(status)` WHERE status IN ('pending', 'processing') — for active claim polling\n\n---\n\n### 2. **referral_kol_rates Table Schema**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` (lines 78-84)\n\n| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------------|-------|\n| `wallet` | TEXT | PRIMARY KEY | KOL wallet address |\n| `rate_bps` | INTEGER | NOT NULL | Custom referrer rate in basis points (e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee) |\n| `set_by` | TEXT | NOT NULL | Admin wallet that set the rate |\n| `created_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NOT NULL, DEFAULT now() | Creation timestamp |\n| `updated_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | NOT NULL, DEFAULT now() | Last update timestamp |\n\n**Purpose:** Overrides the default 1000 bps referrer rate for KOL wallets (e.g., partnership agreements with higher shares)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Environment Variable Patterns for Referral Config**\n\n**Finding:** **No `REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS` env var currently exists** in the backend config.\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/config.ts`\n\nThe `Config` interface (lines 4-23) does NOT include a referral rate field. The backend loads config via:\n- `requireEnv(name: string)` — throws if env var missing\n- `process.env[name] ?? \"defaultValue\"` — optional with fallback\n- `parseInt()` for numeric values\n\n**Current pattern for optional integers with defaults:**\n```typescript\nexport function loadConfig(): Config {\n  return {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    workerPollIntervalMs: parseInt(\n      process.env.WORKER_POLL_INTERVAL_MS ?? \"1000\",\n      10,\n    ),\n    minSolBalance: parseFloat(process.env.MIN_SOL_BALANCE ?? \"0.1\"),\n    // ... more fields ...\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**What needs to be added (based on spec):**\n- Add `referralDefaultRateBps: number` to the `Config` interface\n- Add parsing in `loadConfig()`:\n  ```typescript\n  referralDefaultRateBps: parseInt(\n    process.env.REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS ?? \"1000\",\n    10,\n  ),\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Related Referral Schema (from same migration)**\n\nThe migration also creates these supporting tables (already read above):\n\n- **`referral_codes`** — one custom code per wallet (3-16 chars, [a-z0-9-])\n- **`referral_links`** — immutable referrer→referee binding (one per referee)\n- **`referral_earnings`** — per-game tracking with `referrer_rate_bps` and `referee_rebate_rate_bps` (always 1000 for v1)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Default Rate Constants from Spec**\n\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md`:\n\n- **Default referrer rate:** 1000 bps of total fee (= 50 bps of wager)\n- **Referee rebate:** Always 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable)\n- **KOL override:** Stored in `referral_kol_rates.rate_bps`, applied at settlement time\n\n**Gap identified in spec (line 132